          <text><![CDATA[<p>Expresses the sense of the House of Representatives that:</p> <UL> <LI>the trial and conviction of 50 African-American sailors for mutiny in connection with their service at the Port Chicago Naval Magazine in Concord, California, during World War II were wrongfully pursued because of racial prejudice; and <LI>Congress should publicly exonerate the 50 sailors to further aid in healing the racial divide that continues to exist in the United States. </LI> </UL>]]></text>
